<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF99EF5AFF12F9A7FC0EF920" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF99EF5AFF12F9A7FC0EF920" blockId="49.[151,1436,1554,1689]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<materialsCitation id="EDAC0636FF99EF5AFF12F9A7FC02F920" location="Neartic Region" municipality="Neotropical Region" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Parana">
The tribe is composed by five genera and 56 species, distributed in the 
<collectingMunicipality id="BD1F9611FF99EF5AFC47F9A7FB17F994" box="[962,1186,1554,1580]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Neotropical Region</collectingMunicipality>
, even if a few species reach the Mexican Transition Zone and the 
<location id="581B5AB0FF99EF5AFD06F983FC87F9E8" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:D56DBD7DFF99EF5AFF12FA7FFC0EF920:581B5AB0FF99EF5AFD06F983FC87F9E8" box="[643,818,1590,1616]" municipality="Neotropical Region" name="Neartic Region" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" stateProvince="Parana">Neartic Region</location>
. Identification keys for almost all species are available since an extensive revision of the tribe was carried out so far (
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFF99EF5AFCCBF9EFFC52F9CC" author="Emsley, M." box="[846,999,1626,1652]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 248" refId="ref31846" refString="Emsley, M. (1970) A revision of the Steirodontine katydids (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae: Steirodontini). Academy of Natural Sciences, 122, 125 - 248." type="journal article" year="1970">Emsley 1970</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record of the tribe for the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF99EF5AFF45F9CBFEFAF920" box="[192,335,1662,1688]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
, as we found five species inhabiting the sampling sites
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
